import React , { useMemo }from 'react' export default function Model3D({ report }) { const boxitem = useMemo(() => { if (report && report.length) { const latestData = report[report.length - 1]; return [ { title: 'Số ca nhiễm', count: latestData.Confirmed, type: 'confirmed', }, { title: 'Khỏi', count: latestData.Recovered, type: 'recovered', }, { title: 'Tử vong', count: latestData.Deaths, type: 'death', }, ]; } return []; }, [report]); return ( < div className='model_box'>

  • Total number of infections { boxitem.map((data)=> ( {data} )) }
  • Total dose provided
    10,693.141

  • Number of deaths
    10,693.141
  • Number of people who received
    the full dose
    10,693.141

"Total dose delivered" is the number of doses of vaccine given to everyone. Because some vaccines require multiple doses, the number of people who have had the full dose of the vaccine may be lower.The "full dose" is the number of people who have had the full dose of COVID-19 vaccine.

) }
